        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 8 at 2:43AM CDT by NWS Hastings NE</headline>
        <description>At 243 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Ruskin, or 22 miles northwest of Belleville, moving east at 35 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

This strong thunderstorm will be near...
Deshler around 250 AM CDT.

Other locations in the path of this storm include Hubbell.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
